Date: Tue, 22 Apr 1997 17:09:49 -0400
From: John Gawoski <jgawoski@warren.med.harvard.edu>
Television and videotape standards
With respect to the recent postings on videotapes of "The Coming Plague", my
recollection is that TV around the world has different technical standards
(lines scanned per inch differ, for example). That is, to view an American
or Canadian programme taped directly to videotape, I think one will need a TV
made for that market. I don't remember if that is also true of the videotape
machine. I believe that it is possible to convert between formats, but that
this in essence requires making a new tape. Subscribers outside the US or
Canada may wish to verify this before purchasing videotapes intended for sale
here. Perhaps someone with more technical expertise can clarify, as my
experience is somewhat dated.
---
John Gawoski, M.D.
Department of Laboratory Medicine
Lahey Hitchcock Clinic
41 Mall Road
Burlington, MA 01805 USA
617.273.8935
e-mail: <jgawoski@warren.med.harvard.edu>
[Absolutely correct. -- Mod CHC]
